description:
&lt;p&gt;This is an exciting opportunity to join an expanding and ambitious team. We are looking for someone who is interested in the application of technology to learning, who will provide high quality support to subject matter experts (SME’s) as they convert training over to a more blended or on-line approach. Trouble shooting any software or hardware issues.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The post holder will provide knowledge and technical support to SME’s for the design and / or conversion of training to on-line, virtual delivery or using technology to enhance face to face training. A diverse and exciting role which could involve producing video assets one day, being involved in the development of Medical Education Simulations or virtual training through Adobe Connect another or just helping a Trainer to enhance a Powerpoint presentation.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Providing outstanding customer service by acting as a first point of contact to managers and staff, supporting their access to statutory and mandatory training. Assisting the Training Administration Team to report on statutory and mandatory training locally and nationally, so we can understand better where support is needed.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This role would suit someone with an excellent understanding of IT and an interest in being involved in innovative and creative ways to use technology to enhance learning.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Previous applicants need not apply.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Working hours: 37.5 hours per week, Monday to Friday&lt;/p&gt;
